<item>
            <title>[LU-3444] Provide conclusive evidence that obdfilter_survey is not distructive.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3444</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Following recent discussion, recorded on &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-146&quot; title=&quot;Use of obdfilter_survey is cautioned against unnecessarily on production file systems&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LUDOC-146&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUDOC-146&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, we have added some vague language to hedge against the remote possibility that obdfilter_survey might destroy your file system.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be valuable to have conclusive evidence that obdfilter_survey is (or isn&apos;t safe) to use on a production file system.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="19315">LU-3444</key>
            <summary>Provide conclusive evidence that obdfilter_survey is not distructive.</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=11303&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
