                                                                                <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>2</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="60156" author="brian" created="Fri, 7 Jun 2013 10:16:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;And if the conclusion is that it is non-destructive and safe to run on a production file system, and we say as much in the manual, then even more important than all of that is to create/always-run a regression test that ensures that it remains safe, for every release!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Not that I have any recollection of that ever regressing, but we&apos;d be in some very hot water if ever it did.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
